# mnemo-note npm README / LICENSE (do not regress)

For the **repo root** package `mnemo-note` (`package.json` at the monorepo root):

1. **`package.json` → `"files"`** must **always** include **`README.md`** and **`LICENSE`** explicitly, in addition to `bin`, `dist`, and `examples`.
2. **Never remove** those two entries to “rely on npm defaults.” Although `npm pack` often includes them anyway, **npmjs.com has shown the package page without a README** when they were not listed (see CHANGELOG **2.1.8** vs **2.1.10**).
3. **`prepublishOnly`** runs **`scripts/verify-npm-package-readme.js`** — if someone drops `README.md` / `LICENSE` from `"files"`, publish will fail.

This does **not** apply to `apps/mnemo-mobile/package.json` or other nested packages unless they are published to npm with the same issue.
